<div class="title">
    <h2>Steps to submit assignment</h2>
</div>
<p>1) Create a Github repository in the name(case-sensitive) of the assignment and clone it.</p>
       <p>For example, if your assignment is <code>web-crawler</code> under java, then the url should be as 
       <% if !current_user.guest? %>
          <code>git@github.com/<%= current_user.username %>/web-crawler</code>.</p>
        <% else %>
            <code>git@github.com/github-username/web-crawler</code>.</p>
        <% end %>
<p>2) Copy the contents of Exercise Folder and Create file(s) in the repository under <code>src/</code> folder, consisting the solution for the exercise.</p>
<p>3) Commit the file(s) and push the changes to github.</p>
<p>4) Copy the latest commit-id </p>
<p>5) Go to the exercise folder (eg ~/hootcode/java/web-crawler) and submit the commit-id to hootcode using 
<pre>hootcode gsubmit commit-id
<br/> eg: hootcode gsubmit aeb9c67gh3j6k78fdgth</pre>
<p>6) You can make your changes in the github repository and  follow the steps 3 to 5 to reflect the same in Hootcode.</p>


